Others: Detmers allowed two runs on just three hits and two walks while throwing exactly 100 pitches, including 68 for strikes.
His four-seamer -- which averaged 93.8 mph -- and his slider were particularly effective, as each pitch generated eight swinging strikes.
He settled down from there, even striking out Ohtani looking with a 3-2 fastball in the fifth after falling behind in the count.
Detmers retired the last 11 batters he faced, including Will Smith on a strikeout to end the sixth that helped him reach double digits in strikeouts for the fifth time in his career.
